<H3> <TI>   Hanoi Youth Union Involved in Drug Rehabilitation Efforts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2303141694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2303141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hanoi Youth Union implemented anti-drug 
addiction work outlined in the Planning No. 39 of the youth 
union Central Committee with some initial results. 
  It coordinated with the Women's Union and the War Veteran 
Association to encourage 84 people to stop using drugs either at 
home, in drug centers, or in groups in the three pilot subwards 
of Tinh Quang and Cat Linh of Dong Da Precinct and Thanh Duong 
of Hai Ba Trung Precinct. Apart from material assistance, the 
youth union also contacted economic production units to provide 
jobs for the former drug users. 

