<F P=100> NEAR EAST &amp; SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> PAKISTAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Imposes Travel Restrictions on Drug Smugglers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0252D Peshawar MASHRIQ in Urdu 31 Jan 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0252D </F>
<F P=104>  Peshawar MASHRIQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [News Report: "Foreign Travel by Major Drug Smugglers Banned </F>
To Curb Drug Smuggling"] 
  [Text] Islamabad (Bureau Report)--After thorough 
investigation of assets owned at home and abroad by the big fish 
involved in drug smuggling, the federal government has imposed 
restrictions on their leaving the country. According to very 
reliable sources, Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto has given 
instructions to the Pakistan Narcotics Control Board to collect 
information about property and assets owned here and abroad by 
the major drug smugglers and has to send recommendations to the 
home minister. The Narcotics Control Board after a thorough 
investigation has sent its final report to the home minister. 
The home minister has provided final lists of persons involved 
in the drug trade to all related agencies and intelligence 
agencies at all airports in order to take strict action against 
these persons and to make sure they are not able to flee the 
country. These drug smugglers will be fully punished. The 
sources also revealed that in addition to some ministers, 
bureaucrats are also involved in this ugly and detestable trade. 
Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto has given strict instructions to 
the home ministry to rise above political and personal relations 
and to take severe action against these persons who have been 
playing with the lives of our youth. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

