<H3> <TI>   Heroin Smugglers Given Jail Sentences, Fined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0252C Peshawar MASHRIQ in Urdu 13 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0252C </F>
<F P=104>  Peshawar MASHRIQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [News Report: "Arrested Drug Smugglers Given Jail Term, </F>
Fines"] 
  [Text] Peshawar (Staff Reporter)--The Peshawar courts 
sentenced two persons to a total jail term of seven years, fines 
of 15,000 rupees, and 15 lashes while trying two cases of drug 
smuggling. Khan Akbar Khan, district and session judge of 
Peshawar, sentenced Amirzada of Bara Gate to three years hard 
labor, a 5,000 rupee fine, and five lashes for possession of 
five kilogram of heroin. It is important to mention here that 
this person was arrested by Paskhara police in 1988 for 
possession of drugs. Meanwhile, in another drug-related case, 
Shah Jehan Khan, additional district and session judge of 
Peshawar, has sentenced Ghulam Jaib of Mardan for four years of 
hard labor, ten lashes, and a 10,000 rupees fine for a similar 
crime. In case of failure to pay the fine the accused will serve 
an additional six months in jail. It should be known that the 
Narcotics Police had recovered 250 grams of opium and 200 grams 
of heroin from the accused's person last year during a bus 
search at Bara check post. 

</TEXT>

