<H3> <TI>   Pakistani Executed For Heroin Smuggling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2503121994 Riyadh Saudi Arabian Kingdom Radio Network in 
Arabic 1130 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2503121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh Saudi Arabian Kingdom Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Interior Ministry has issued a statement on 
the execution of Muhammad Sulayman Kul Hasan, a Pakistani 
national, who had been found guilty of smuggling a quantity of 
heroin into the Kingdom. [passage omitted] 
  Thanks to God, Muhammad Sulayman Kul Hasan, a Pakistani 
national, was arrested while he was smuggling a quantity of 
heroin into the Kingdom. The investigation found him guilty of 
the charges against him. The court then sentenced him to be 
beheaded with a sword. The sentence was approved by the 
permanent bodies of the Higher Judicial Council. Royal decree 
No 4/1263/M issued on 11 Sha'ban 1414 AH authorized the 
execution of the sentence. 
  Muhammad Sulayman Kul Hasan was beheaded in the city of 
Jeddah, region of Mecca, on Friday 13 Sha'ban 1414 AH [25 March 
1994]. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

