<H3> <TI>   Large Heroin Seizure Reported in Trieste </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2103203894 London Kanal-6 Television in Turkish 1600 GMT 
21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2103203894 </F>
<F P=104>  London Kanal-6 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Some 300 kg of heroin was seized in a Turkish truck 
in Trieste in northern Italy. Its market price is $294 million. 
It was reported that this record amount of narcotic material 
was destined for Austria, Italy, Germany, and the Netherlands, 
and that two people have been detained in connection with the 
incident. It was found out that the truck was brought to the 
Trieste port on the "Kaptan Abidin Doran" ferry. It was learned 
that the ferry belongs to Maritime Transportation. 

</TEXT>

