<H3> <TI>   `Historic' Cocaine Seizure in Amsterdam </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103172894 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1600 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels La Une Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A historic seizure for Amsterdam's customs officers; 
they seized 2.5 tonnes of cocaine in a warehouse this weekend. 
The Dutch police also arrested 14 people. The cocaine came 
from Venezuela. It had arrived in Amsterdam by ship. The 
street value of the drugs is colossal: The cocaine would have 
fetched some 3.5 billion Belgian francs, but it was destroyed by 
Dutch customs officers. 

