<H3> <TI>   Three Arrested Attempting To Sell 24 Kg of Hashish to Military Units </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2103104094 Istanbul SABAH in Turkish 8 Mar 94 p 20 </F>
<F P=103> NC2103104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul SABAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The security forces have arrested three village 
guards for trying to sell 24 kg of hashish to the military units 
in Van. Acting on information, the teams affiliated with the 
gendarmerie regiment command headquarters contacted Hadi Haras, 
a village guard in Konalga in Catak district, who also has a 
business in Van, and agreed to buy the hashish in his 
possession. They arrested Hadi Haras, Haci Haras, and Ahmet 
Haras when they delivered 24 kg of hashish to the teams on the 
outskirts of Kurubas. The three drug traffickers have been 
detained. 

