<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> TAJIKISTAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drug Smugglers Detained on Border With Afghanistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903095394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1903095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last night, on a section of the Iskashimskiy "Pamir" 
frontier detachment, Russian border guards thwarted an attempt 
by smugglers to take narcotics from Afghanistan to Tajikistan. 
The Tajik KHOVAR agency learned from military sources that 
there was an armed clash between the border guards and the 
infiltrators. There were no casualties among the servicemen. 
Two smugglers were detained. Of late, this is not the first 
instance of contraband deals between Afghans and locals. 
Recently, Russian border guards detained about 20 smugglers who 
tried to take a consignment from Afghan to Tajik territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-22107 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "jpten003__l94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   JPRS-TEN-94-003-L </AU>
Document Type:JPRS 
Document Title:Environmental Issues 

