<F P=101> MONGOLIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ulaanbaatar, Moscow Sign Environmental Protection Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1502221394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1823 GMT 15 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1502221394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 15 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Today 
here signed was the agreement on cooperation between Mongolia 
and the Russian Federation in the sphere of nature and 
environment protection. 
  In the agreement reflected is the number of concrete issues 
of cooperation, including an issue about foundation of an 
international park for rare animals by efforts of the two 
neighboring countries. 
  The agreement was signed by the Minister of Nature and 
Environment Protection of Mongolia G. Batjargal, the Minister of 
Protection of Environment and Natural Resources of the Russian 
Federation V.I. Danilov-Danilyan. The member of the Russian 
Government, member of the Duma, minister of the Russian 
Federation was received today by the Prime Minister of Mongolia 
P. Jasray, who expressed satisfaction apropos of the meeting 
with the first representative of the government of the Russian 
Federation after it was recently formed. 
  The sides exchanged information about situation in their 
countries, measures being take by the governments of the two 
countries the deputy-premier of Mongolia, chairman of the 
Mongolian part of the Inter-Government Mongolian-Russian 
Commission C. Purebdorj, and other officials participated in the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

