Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [UK press release from the Prime Minister's Office: "Taking </F>
Rio Forward - UK Panel On Sustainable Development"] 
  [Text] The Prime Minister, the Rt Hon [Right Honorable] 
John Major MP, today announced the appointment of a new 
independent panel to advise Government on the implementation of 
"Sustainable Development: The UK Strategy." 
  The Panel is to be convened by Sir Crispin Tickell. The 
other 
members are Lord Selborne, Lord Alexander of Weedon, Sir John 
Houghton and Dr Anne McLaren. 
  It will give independent advice to the Government and will 
be 
consulted on issues of major strategic importance for 
sustainable development. 
  The Prime Minister has given the Panel a specific charge: to 
keep in view general sustainability issues at home and abroad, 
to identify major problems or opportunities likely to arise, to 
monitor progress and to consider questions of priority. 

