<H3> <TI>   Agreement Reached With Brazil on Environmental Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2202064794 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 
1630 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2202064794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi Doordarshan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India and Brazil are to cooperate in the fields of 
forestry, pollution control and waste management. This was 
announced after talks between the environment minister, Mr. 
Kamalnath, and his Brazilian counterpart, Mr. Rubens Ricupero, 
in New Delhi today. Mr. Ricupero offered Brazilian know-how for 
using alcohol as a substitute for petrol. He sought Indian 
assistance in environment audit. 

</TEXT>

